# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __le__, __gt__, __ge__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# decimal.Decimal: __le__ = true (Decimal objects support <= numeric ordering),
# __gt__ = true (Decimal objects support > numeric ordering),
# __ge__ = true (Decimal objects support >= numeric ordering).
# This true/true/true pattern is the key finding of wave 676 for the decimal
# module: Decimal fully implements the upper-bound and strict ordering protocols.
# All other decimal classes (Context, DecimalException, InvalidOperation,
# Overflow, Underflow): false for all three operators.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

